info.senderName: NWS Cheyenne (Southeastern Wyoming and Western Nebraska)
info.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 26 at 7:11PM MST until February 27 at 8:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 AM MST MONDAY... * WHAT...Southwest winds 35 to 45 MPH with gusts up to 70 MPH. * WHERE...Portions of southeast Wyoming, including the South Laramie Range and Foothills, Platte, Goshen, Laramie, and northern Carbon Counties. * WHEN...Until 8 AM MST Monday. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight or high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 MPH or gusts of 58 MPH or more can lead to property damage.
